- Bean and Bacon Breakfast Burrito
   - Estimated serving size: 1 burrito
   - Calories per serving: 400

   - List of ingredients:
     - 2 slices of bacon
     - 1/2 cup of canned beans
     - 2 eggs
     - 1 large tortilla
     - Salt and pepper to taste
     - Optional toppings: cheese, salsa, avocado

   - Step-by-step instructions:
     1. Cook bacon in a skillet until crispy. Remove from skillet and chop into small pieces.
     2. In the same skillet, heat canned beans until warmed through.
     3. In a separate bowl, whisk eggs and season with salt and pepper.
     4. Scramble eggs in the skillet until fully cooked.
     5. Place the tortilla on a flat surface and layer the beans, bacon, and scrambled eggs in the center.
     6. Add any optional toppings you desire.
     7. Fold the sides of the tortilla in and roll it up tightly.
     8. Heat the burrito in the skillet for a few minutes on each side until lightly browned.
     9. Serve hot and enjoy your delicious bean and bacon breakfast burrito!

- Baked Chicken Thighs with Wild Rice Pilaf and Roasted Asparagus

- Baked Chicken Thighs with Wild Rice Pilaf and Roasted Asparagus
- Estimated serving size: 4 servings 🍽️
- Calories per serving: Approximately 400 calories 🔥

- List of ingredients:
  - 4 bone-in, skin-on chicken thighs
  - 1 cup wild rice
  - 2 cups chicken broth
  - 1 bunch of asparagus
  - Olive oil
  - Salt and pepper
  - Optional: herbs or spices of your choice

- Step-by-step instructions:
1. Preheat your oven to 400°F (200°C).
2. Season the chicken thighs with salt, pepper, and any herbs or spices you like. Place them on a baking sheet and bake for about 35-40 minutes or until cooked through.
3. While the chicken is baking, rinse the wild rice and cook it according to the package instructions, using chicken broth instead of water for added flavor.
4. Trim the woody ends off the asparagus and place them on a separate baking sheet. Drizzle with olive oil, season with salt and pepper, and roast in the oven for about 15-20 minutes.
5. Once everything is cooked, plate the wild rice pilaf, top with the baked chicken thighs, and serve with the roasted asparagus on the side. Enjoy your delicious and nutritious meal! 🍗🍚🌱

- Garlic Butter Shrimp Pasta
- Estimated serving size: 4
- Calories per serving: 400
- List of ingredients:
  - 1 lb shrimp, peeled and deveined
  - 8 oz spaghetti noodles
  - 4 cloves garlic, minced
  - 4 tbsp butter
  - Salt and pepper to taste
  - Fresh parsley for garnish
  - Mixed greens for side salad
  - Dressing of choice for salad

- Step-by-step instructions:
1. Cook spaghetti noodles according to package instructions. Drain and set aside.
2. In a large skillet, melt butter over medium heat. Add minced garlic and cook until fragrant.
3. Add shrimp to the skillet and cook until pink and cooked through, about 2-3 minutes per side.
4. Season shrimp with salt and pepper to taste.
5. Add cooked spaghetti noodles to the skillet and toss with the garlic butter shrimp.
6. Serve shrimp and pasta on a plate, garnish with fresh parsley.
7. Serve with mixed greens salad on the side dressed with your favorite dressing.
8. Enjoy your garlic butter shrimp pasta with a side salad of mixed greens!

- BLT Rice Bowls
- Estimated serving size: 4 servings 🍽️
- Calories per serving: Approximately 400 calories 🔥
- Ingredients:
  - 2 cups cooked white or brown rice
  - 8 slices of crispy bacon, crumbled
  - 1 cup diced tomatoes
  - 2 cups chopped lettuce
  - 1/2 cup creamy ranch dressing

- Step-by-step instructions:
1. Cook the rice according to package instructions and divide it into four bowls.
2. Top each bowl of rice with equal amounts of crispy bacon, diced tomatoes, and chopped lettuce.
3. Drizzle a generous amount of creamy ranch dressing over the top.
4. Serve and enjoy your delicious BLT Rice Bowls!

- Baked Sweet Potato with Seasoned Ground Turkey and Steamed Broccoli
- Estimated serving size: 1
- Calories per serving: 400

Ingredients:
- 1 medium sweet potato
- 4 oz lean ground turkey
- 1/2 tsp olive oil
- 1/4 tsp garlic powder
- 1/4 tsp onion powder
- 1/4 tsp paprika
- Salt and pepper to taste
- 1 cup broccoli florets

Instructions:
1. Preheat the oven to 400°F (200°C).
2. Wash and scrub the sweet potato, then pierce it with a fork a few times.
3. Place the sweet potato on a baking sheet and bake for 45-60 minutes, or until tender.
4. While the sweet potato is baking, heat olive oil in a skillet over medium heat.
5. Add the ground turkey, garlic powder, onion powder, paprika, salt, and pepper to the skillet. Cook until the turkey is browned and fully cooked.
6. Steam the broccoli florets either on the stovetop or in the microwave until tender.
7. Once the sweet potato is cooked, slice it open and fluff the insides.
8. Top the sweet potato with the seasoned ground turkey and serve with steamed broccoli on the side.
9. Enjoy your nutritious and flavorful meal!

- Baked Chicken with Roasted Potatoes and Caramelized Onions

- Baked Chicken with Roasted Potatoes and Caramelized Onions
- Estimated serving size: 4
- Calories per serving: 400

- Ingredients:
  - 4 chicken breasts
  - 4 large potatoes, diced
  - 2 onions, sliced
  - 2 tbsp olive oil
  - 2 tbsp balsamic vinegar
  - Salt and pepper to taste
  - 1 tsp garlic powder
  - 1 tsp paprika
  - Fresh herbs (optional)

- Step-by-step instructions:
1. Preheat your oven to 400°F (200°C).
2. Season the chicken breasts with salt, pepper, garlic powder, and paprika. Place them on a baking dish.
3. In a separate bowl, toss the diced potatoes with olive oil, salt, and pepper. Spread them on a baking sheet in a single layer.
4. Place the baking dish with the chicken and the baking sheet with the potatoes in the oven. Bake for 20 minutes.
5. Meanwhile, heat some olive oil in a pan and add the sliced onions. Cook over low heat until caramelized, about 15-20 minutes.
6. After the initial 20 minutes of baking, add the caramelized onions on top of the chicken and drizzle balsamic vinegar.
7. Continue baking for an additional 10-15 minutes, or until the chicken is cooked through and the potatoes are crispy on the edges.
8. Serve the baked chicken with roasted potatoes and caramelized onions, garnish with fresh herbs if desired. Enjoy!
